20/06/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign Minister Ilir Meta and Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Musa Xhaferri met on Thursday (19 June) and agreed to open two new border crossings near the cities of Debar and Struga.
The officials also discussed the need for more dynamic bilateral relations, especially in regards to economic co-operation and security.
(A1 TV - 19/06/03)
